INTEGRATED STAR & SALARY SYSTEM FOR ITHU (Ages 5–15)
Phase 1: Ages 5–9 – Star-Based Reward System

Goal: Build motivation, consistency, and a sense of achievement

Star Chart Categories (daily/weekly basis):

Completed study task (1 star)

Showed focus without distractions (2 stars)

Helped at home or showed kindness (1–2 stars)

Learned something new independently (3 stars)

Weekly review or presentation (5 stars)

Star to Currency Conversion:

Every 10 stars = ₹10 or 1 Ithu Coin

Use Ithu Coins in a Reward Store (snacks, toys, outings, or time with a special activity)

Banking Practice:

Keep a star ledger

Encourage saving vs. spending

Introduce simple interest (e.g., saving 50 stars = bonus 5 stars)

Phase 2: Ages 10–12 – Hybrid System: Stars + Salary

Goal: Introduce structured earnings like salary

Assign monthly salary (e.g., ₹200/month) based on fulfilling duties like:

Weekly academic reports

Managing study plan independently

Helping others (teaching sibling, etc.)

Stars still earned for extra tasks or above-and-beyond efforts

Encourage budgeting:

Divide into: Save (50%), Spend (30%), Donate or Invest (20%)

Use notebooks or simple apps for tracking

Phase 3: Ages 13–15 – Full Salary System (Mini Internship Style)

Goal: Real-world financial literacy & responsibility

Monthly “Salary” (₹500–1000 range depending on complexity)

Paid for managing own learning

Completing larger projects (blog, robotics demo, app, art exhibit)

Optional “bonuses” for skill certifications, competition wins, etc.

Investment & Entrepreneurship:

Encourage him to "invest" in his own projects (buy a domain, build app)

Use mock stocks, saving plans, or even mini vending business